{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-fill-in-the-blank-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-have-a-conversation-about-preferences-and-motivations/task-56","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Vežba 56","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Encourage</span> znači dati nekome pomoć ili samopouzdanje da nešto uradi. Na primer, kada tvoj prijatelj kaže, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">You can solve this coding problem!</span> on te ohrabruje.</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Discourage</span> je suprotno tome; znači da se neko čini nesigurnim ili da ne voli nešto raditi. Ako taj prijatelj kaže, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">That programming language is too hard for beginners</span>, može vas obeshrabriti za učenje toga.</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Discouraging</span> opisuje nešto što vas čini očajnim. Kao što je, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Finding a bug in your code after hours of work can be discouraging.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Encouraging</span> je mesto gde nešto daje hrabrost ili nadu. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Getting your first program to run is very encouraging.</span></p>\n</section>","instructions":"","explanation":null,"challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-have-a-conversation-about-preferences-and-motivations","lang":"en-US","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-have-a-conversation-about-preferences-and-motivations/task-56"},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>I hear you, Tom. BLANK in meetings for hours can be BLANK.</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"Sitting","feedback":"<p>Ova reč opisuje čin sedenja. Piše se velikim slovima.</p>"},{"answer":"discouraging","feedback":"<p>Ova reč znači nešto što te čini da se ne osećaš samouvereno ili da ne želiš da nastaviš. Završava sa <span class=\"highlig